# {{context|transitive|obsolete|historical}} To cause one to renounce or recant. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive}} To [[reject]] with [[solemnity]]; to abandon [[forever]]; to [[repudiate]]; to [[disclaim]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: ''To abjure errors.''
#* '''1610''', ''[[s:The Tempest|The Tempest]]'', by [[w:William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]], act 5 scene 1
#*: But this rough magic I here '''abjure''' [...]
# {{context|transitive}} To abstain from; to [[avoid]]; to [[shun]].

